==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tyrotoxicon
<hw>Tyr`o*tox"i*con</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ cheese + <?/. See <er>Toxic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld>
<def>A ptomaine discovered by Vaughan in putrid cheese and other dairy
products, and producing symptoms similar to cholera infantum.
Chemically, it appears to be related to, or identical with,
diazobenzol.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tyrotoxine</ent>⟦br⟧
